# wav2vec2 audio frame classification

Code used for the paper ["Detection of Prosodic Boundaries in Speech Using Wav2Vec 2.0" (TSD 2022)](https://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-3-031-16270-1_31)

(This repository is a work in progress)

![w2v2](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/48019906/193046350-37b1616c-e3e8-497e-b5ed-19c0c0ccb027.png)

## Prosodic boundary detection

### Code:

- **data preparation:** *to be added later (code needs some cleaning)*

  in the meantime, follow the example below (JSON format)
  
  wav files should be split into intervals of max. 30s (depends on the size of the model and the amount of available memory) and the sample rate must be 16kHz
  
- **training and prediction:** `wav2vec2_audioFrameClassification/wav2vec2_audioFrameClassification.py`

  see `wav2vec2_audioFrameClassification/run.sh` for an example of how to use
- **evaluation:** *to be added later (code needs some cleaning)*

### Requirements:

`wav2vec2_audioFrameClassification.py` requires

- Python 3.6+
- torch
- datasets
- transformers

Oldest versions that have been confirmed to work: torch 1.10.0, datasets 1.14.0, transformers 4.18.0

### Examples:
